    <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: left;">A House That <span>Stopped Talking</span></h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.8;">
      Frank used to be the loud one. Game nights, bad jokes at dinner, the dad who embarrassed his kids on purpose. Then he lost his job. Then his father got sick. Then the silence in the house got so loud nobody could hear over it. His twelve-year-old son started hiding in his room. His teenage daughter stopped coming home for dinner. His wife stopped asking how his day was.
    </p>
    <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.8;">
      It was Frank who finally picked up the phone. A neighbor mentioned Reach For Youth. He called the next morning, sitting in his truck in the driveway, before he could talk himself out of it.
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: left;">Saying It <span>Out Loud</span></h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.8;">
      The family started weekly counseling with one of RFY&rsquo;s licensed clinicians. The first few sessions were rough. Old hurts came up. Things got said. But the therapist held the space the way a good coach holds a team &mdash; firm, fair, and absolutely on everyone&rsquo;s side at the same time.
    </p>
    <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.8;">
      &ldquo;I learned I had been protecting my family from my own feelings,&rdquo; Frank said. &ldquo;Turns out that wasn&rsquo;t protecting them at all. It was leaving them out.&rdquo;
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: left;">Small <span>Repairs</span></h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.8;">
      Together, the family built new habits. A check-in at dinner where everyone shared one good thing and one hard thing. A standing Saturday morning walk for Frank and his daughter. A weekly board game night that pulled his son out of his room. Nothing dramatic. Just consistent, repeated proof that they could show up for each other.
    </p>

    <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: left;">A Family <span>Again</span></h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.8;">
      Two years later, Frank still keeps the appointment card from his first session in his wallet. The family doesn&rsquo;t need weekly therapy anymore, but they go in for tune-ups when life gets heavy. He says calling RFY was the best decision he&rsquo;s ever made.
    </p>

    <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-primary); font-weight: 600; text-align: center; margin-top: var(--space-2xl); padding: var(--space-xl); background: rgba(114,242,206,0.15); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
      &ldquo;We didn&rsquo;t lose our family. We just needed help finding our way back to it.&rdquo;
    </p>

